-- Lowe's to build California distribution center
-- 
-- Wed Jan 10, 2007 7:52am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/10/us-lowes-idUSWEN203420070110

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Lowe's Cos., the world's No. 2 home improvement retailer, on Wednesday announced 

 plans for a new flatbed distribution center in the Port of Stockton, California. The company plans to retrofit two 120,000-square-foot buildings. It said the facility will supply products to more than 40 retail stores in northern California, Nevada and Oregon, and initially employ 35 people. Shipping operations are slated to begin in the first half of this year, Lowe's said.